[8]Subsequently, it was referred to as the T-34 because the lifting capacity of the airship was about 34 tons.Before being disassembled to be moved via ship to the United States, the airship made several test flights, mainly in the surroundings of Rome.
[9]In one of these flights was a guest on board the then us ambassador, Robert Johnson Underwood; on this occasion, the Roma came to fly over Naples and the island of Capri.The first flight to the United States took place on the 15th November, 1921, from the base of Langley in Virginia.
